<sect1 id="sec.suse.virt.konsolen">
 <title>Virtual Consoles</title><indexterm>

 <primary>consoles</primary>

 <secondary>switching</secondary></indexterm>

 <para>
  Linux is a multiuser and multitasking system. The advantages of these
  features can be appreciated even on a stand-alone PC system. In text mode,
  there are six virtual consoles available. Switch between them using
  <keycombo> <keycap function="alt"/> <keycap>F1</keycap> </keycombo> through
  <keycombo> <keycap function="alt"/> <keycap>F6</keycap> </keycombo>. The
  seventh console is reserved for X and the tenth console shows kernel
  messages. <!--taroth 2014-03-07: /etc/inittab no longer exists:
   More or fewer consoles can be assigned by modifying the file
  <filename>/etc/inittab</filename>.-->
 </para><indexterm>

 <primary>consoles</primary>

 <secondary>assigning</secondary></indexterm><indexterm>

 <primary>configuration files</primary>

 <!--<secondary>inittab</secondary>--></indexterm>

 <para>
  To switch to a console from X without shutting it down, use <keycombo>
  <keycap function="control"/> <keycap function="alt"/> <keycap>F1</keycap> </keycombo>
  to <keycombo> <keycap function="control">Ctrl</keycap> <keycap function="alt"/>
  <keycap>F6</keycap> </keycombo>. To return to X, press <keycombo>
  <keycap function="alt"/> <keycap>F7</keycap> </keycombo>.
 </para>
</sect1>
